    <title type="display">Sammy&#8217;s Law</title>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Sammy&#8217;s Law</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To require large social media platform providers to create, maintain, and make available to third-party safety software providers a set of real-time application programming interfaces, through which a child or a parent or legal guardian of a child may delegate permission to a third-party safety software provider to manage the online interactions, content, and account settings of such child on the large social media platform on the same terms as such child, and for other purposes.</title>
